products.notes:
Notes

3M™ Heat Shrink Cable Sleeve MDT isa flame retardant sleeve offers reliable performance for electrical splices, connections and terminations. The factory applied, heat activated, thermoplastic sealant acts as a barrier against adverse environmental conditions. It is fast shrinking for easy handling and installation while maintaining maximum operating reliability and system protection. It withstands temperatures of 67 to 230 degrees F ( 55 to 110 degrees C). ABS, SAE AS23053/15, Class 2 Certified and RoHS 2011/65/EU Compliant.
  • Superior resistance to abrasion, corrosion and chemicals
  • Offers reliable performance for electrical splices, connections and terminations
  • Suitable for large transitions, splices and battery cables
  • Made of black cross-linked polyolefin
  • Withstands temperatures of -67 to 230 degrees F (-55 to 110 degrees C)
  • Flame-retardant
3M™ Heat Shrink Cable Sleeve MDT is a flexible, medium wall tubing that provides abrasion, corrosion and chemical resistance. This sleeve has a 3:1 shrink ratio that offers primary electrical insulation for 1 kV rated applications. The flame retardant polyolefin construction features a thermoplastic sealant to provide moisture seal protection.

attributes.specification: SAE AS23053/5 Class 1, MIL-STD-202, RoHs Compliant, UL224, CSA C 22.2 No 198.1

products.notes:
Notes

Epson LabelWorks PX heat shrink labels provider a secure, durable and legible alternative for marking wires, cords, and network cables. With our continuous roll heat shrink label cartridges, you choose the length of the label, as well as the margin settings so you never waste material or have to trim long labels with a scissors. Our heat shrink labels offer industry-leading resistance to abrasives, chemicals, and weather to ensure applications remain legible even under more extreme conditions. In terms of flexibility, Epson LabelWorks heat shrink labels remain flexible and legible in applications where they are tested constantly.
  • Industrial grade polyolefin base material
  • Shrink ratio of 3:1
  • Compliant to UL 224 and CSA C 22.2 No. 198.1
  • Rated Temp: 125° C
  • Rated Voltage 600V/ATF

  • Refill with Master Ultratane Butane for best performance

  • Combo Pack includes mini-trigger torch and palm-sized micro torch

products.title: #12/2 20 Amp 600V 250' Armorlite® Aluminum MC Lite Cable (Priced per Ft)

attributes.application: Convey power from the service drop to the meter base and from the meter base to the distribution panelboard

products.notes:
Notes

Southwire Armorlite ® Type MC Cable is constructed with soft-drawn copper, Type THHN/THWN conductors rated 90°C dry available in sizes 14 AWG through 2 AWG, and a green insulated grounding conductor. The conductors are cabled together and a binder tape bearing the print legend is wrapped around the assembly. Aluminum interlocking armor is applied over the assembly.
  • Branch, feeder and service power distribution in commercial, industrial, institutional, and multiresidential buildings
  • Fished or embedded in plaster
  • Concealed or exposed installations
  • Installation in cable tray and approved raceways
Branch, feeder and service power distribution in commercial, industrial, institutional, and multi-residential buildings. Power, lighting, control, and signal circuits. Fished or embedded in plaster. Concealed or exposed installations. Environmental air-handling spaces per NEC 300.22 (C). Places of Assembly per NEC 518.4 and theaters per NEC 520.5. Installation in cable tray and approved raceways. Under raised floors for information technology equipment conductors and cables per NEC 645.5(D) & 645.5(D)(2). Class I Div. 2, Class II Div 2, & Class III Div. 1 Hazardous Locations.

Works well with most standard automotive connections and is specified for use in engine compartments where high heat resistance is required by SAE J1128 specifications. Cross-Linking structure reinforces the polyethylene insulation for enhanced durability and resistance to heat and abrasion.
